title: For Sale:  CIA SURVIVAL RIFLE
postcontent: This is a very basic and handy 22LR single-shot survival rifle manufactured by various companies from around the turn of the century until the 1970s (when it was sold as the “Garcia Bronco”). This is an antique in good working condition, likely from the early 1950s, and has no markings other than the “Firearms International Corporation Washington DC 20022” on the inside of the skeletonized buttplate. The Firearms International firm was begun in around 1952 as a front for the CIA to obtain and ship, through supposed commercial sales channels, surplus firearms to allies of the United States during the Cold War. After the Bay of Pigs fiasco, to which they apparently supplied the weapons, the company was outed and reorganized.
